   <taskbody>
      <context class="- topic/section task/context ">During the yearly maintenance, in addition to the semi-annual
battery maintenance it is recommended to perform a battery discharge
test.</context>
      <steps class="- topic/ol task/steps ">
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Make sure the semi-annual battery maintenance was performed.
For more information see <xref href="M_Semi-Annual_Battery_Maintenance_TSK_0000811101.dita"
                     scope="local"
                     type="task"
                     class="- topic/xref "/>.</cmd>
         </step>
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Perform one of the battery discharge tests: </cmd>
            <choices class="- topic/ul task/choices ">
               <choice class="- topic/li task/choice ">Integrated battery test to check the condition and capacity
of the batteries. For more information see <xref href="M_How_to_Start_the_Battery_Test_TSK_0000755300.dita"
                        platform="Modular-DC Modular-AC"
                        scope="local"
                        type="task"
                        class="- topic/xref "/>
                  <xref href="P_How_to_Start_the_Battery_Capacity_Test_TSK_DD00609422.dita"
                        platform="Prime-UPS Prime-Charger"
                        scope="local"
                        type="task"
                        class="- topic/xref "/>.</choice>
               <choice class="- topic/li task/choice ">Battery discharge test according to the manufacturerâ€™s
recommendation, see documentation from the battery manufacture. Record
the following during the test: All cell voltages, discharge current,
overall battery voltage, ambient temperature and discharge time. If
wet cells are used, check the electrolyte temperature of the pilot
cells.<note class="- topic/note ">May require a test load.</note>
               </choice>
            </choices>
         </step>
      </steps>
